<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Hate will live on</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
The ending of the common prayer. He saw the hate in Kerridywnn's eyes. The sorrow in Sarhea's face, the sadistic glee in Morgrist's smile. He had done right. A wedding in the church of Hate should be christened by hate. It was his gift to his friend Drakgeny. The best he could give. <br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>And all</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
Thenic smiled. Kerridwynn chanted the final lines of beseeching to call down their gods Wrath upon him. He knew this was the end of his current role in the Harvesters. He knew his god would be disappointed, but he knew he was doing his job. And thats all he could do.<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>live in Hate.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
With pain in her eyes, Kerridywnn murmered something, and Thenic heard the last words as a Harvester<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>goodbye</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
----------------------------------<br>
<br>
Thenic awoke in the priests quarters in the temple. Had she felt remorse? Regret? He would have to ponder this. And now he had all the time he needed to ponder. He returned to his things, scorched, and right where he had sat to die. Kerridwynn walked past him calmly. Everyone else had gone.<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Now you have seen me angry.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
And strode away. He gathered his things, and prepared for a new day with the common prayer.<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>There is hate, and there is rage.....</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
When he finished, he rose and smiled. Today was a new day, and he knew that he would meet it, and imbue in it hate, as he did all things. <br>
<br>
But even with this small solice, all knew that Thenic was again alone.<br>
