<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>He stepped forth into Neriak. His name was Sindeen. His friend kazz had helped him with that much. It was carved on his arm. He had since gotten some real pants from Grobb. A bit baggy, but they would do. A cape, some prayer beads and his magic hammer. <br>
<br>
The hammer had a story all its own. From it, power was drawn. When he touched it to someone who was wounded, they would heal. When he focused on hurting an enemy, they would be struck by a great force. His hammer was his faith.<br>
<br>
Sindeen walked the streets, being greeted with nods from the guards. He walked about trying to recollect something, anything, of this shithole that was his home. Entering a tavern, he overheard an anxious man telling his story</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;I was there when it was said. An attack upon our home! the lightbringers will be marching!&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Sindeen walked over to the barkeep to order a drink and listen in on the conversation as he walked up the barkeep smiled at him </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Aaah! Thenic! Returned already from your haiatus? I guess you'll be having your usual then?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Uuuh. Sure.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Thenic replied, slightly confused. At least now he knew his real name. It was good someone had recognized him. He drank his honey mead, and made some idle conversation, learning a bit about his past. About a group know as the Harvesters of Darkness and about his profession. He was surprized this bartender knew so much about his past. Once he had finished off the mead, he left to seek out these Harvesters in hopes of recovering the rest of his memory. <br>
<br>
But he would have no time. As he left the tavern, a cry was hollared from the gate.<br>
<br>
Lightbringers had entered Nektulos and were on there way to Neriak and quick.<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
He had seen the carnage. Darkelf had slain darkelf. The army of the light was an overbloated rumor. Few had come, and those that had were dispatched. An army of darkelves had then turned on each other, and on a single bowmaster who had single handedly defeated the baron that lead the charge. She had fought in defense of these peoples home, and they hated her for it. Infact, it was for that hate that the lightbringers had even tried to attack. To destroy the heart of Hate.<br>
<br>
<br>
To make war to destroy hate, because they hated hate so much.<br>
<br>
Thenic wondered how it was that he was a darkelf. He felt glad he had lost his memory, because in it he had forgotten hate.<br>
</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
