<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> Thenic walked a long path, sweat beading his forehead. Traveling the path through Highpass hold, while dodging the guards. It seemed today everyone was out to get him, he thought, and only because he sought the past. He thought about todays events. <br>
<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
He had journyed to Neriak to find some answers, but was greeted with only questions and anger. No less than 5 people had challenged him in his supposed home of Neriak, and five times he had fallen. Whatever he had done, whoever he was before, he had angered many, and could not stay in neriak for much longer.<br>
<br>
From there he had left for the swamplands. Beckoned by the rumor of people from this organization he knew only as the Harvesters, he traveled. Ssakas was among those met, and the only to stick in his mind. Ssakas related to him that the Harvesters were being hunted by an empire of some sort because of a single halfelf. He related that there were many of his kind that would wanted him dead for betrayal of the empire, and moreso for association with this halfelf. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;There issss... There is one in particular which hates all of the Harvesters. His hate for them is so great, he had begun a quest to stomp us from the face of Norath, starting with Sarhea. All because the Empire is blind to the truth&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The lizard had said. He had his peoples turn his back on him, and was an outcast, much as Thenic was now.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
&quot;I might not wear an insignia or a badge of the Harvesters, but when this Saurix comes, I'll stand with you against him.&quot;<br>
<br>
---------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>But Saurix had not come for them, but for this mysterious Sarhea. Time past, and they had parted ways as friends.<br>
<br>
They met again briefly a few minutes ago in Highpass, and parted ways again. Thenic could not stay, he had buisiness elsewhere...<br>
<br>
After getting lost 4 times in this marvelous mess of shadowhaven, he had found his way to the trading corner, where people came from all over to haggle and barter goods.<br>
<br>
It was here he met her. Lost in thought, trying to grasp at the last few scraps of hope of finding his past, he sat there, when she walked up. She had been described to him quite well by is friend the bartender, and to a lesser extent by Ssakas, but there was no mistaking it. She walked up to him with a slightly surprized look on her face. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Goodday Kerridwynn.&quot; <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:yellow;font-family:verdana;font-size:small;">Thenic N'Ryt</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:century gothic;font-size:medium;">Healer in service to Innoruuk</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-family:georgia;font-size:small;">Wanderer,</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:century gothic;font-size:small;"> Healer,</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;font-family:georgia;font-size:small;">Teir'dal</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dender>dender</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(2/6/03 8:41:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/fharvestersofdarknessfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A Reminder</span><hr size=1> ((Part five of the story that never ends... the next one will be short, and wrap it up.))<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> It was her, the one called Illharess. Clad all in black, and wearing barely veiled hate on her face. Finally, Thenic had caught a break, and had found at least one person who could tell him about his past. He asked her many questions, including about the carved scar on his arm, which she knew naught about. She told him much, but these words resounded in his mind for hours</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Xas, you were once a follower of the Scythe. You were accepted as a member of the hall, and as member of the family. But you betrayed us, you broke the trust we gave you. And I do not know why&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>She left, but not before extending to him the location of the new Harvester hall in Shadowhaven. It burned within him. The curiousity of why he had done what he had, and why he had lost his memories of it all. Perhaps a visit to the hall would help him find what he searched for.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> Kiyda had been there. He hadn't known she was a member of the Scythe. It made more sense now though; often when travelling, he would happen across her, almost as if she was checking up on him. She said that they had fought in the past, and both she and Thenic agreed that maybe it was better than he was without his memories... he was a horrible person it seemed... so vicious and antagonizing. <br>
<br>
He talked with her, the sage Morgrist, and the overactive Babed. He'd shown them the mark on his arm as well <br>
<br>
Morgrist took a look at it. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> &quot;I do not know exactly what this means. Often slaves are marked with the names of their owners or of those who capture them. It is a common practice.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Grrr... This name seems familiar to me. Someone from the Sisters of Myth, god knows it wouldn't be beneth them to take a Teir'dal.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> Hissed Kiyda, obviously angry.<br>
<br>
Morgrist rubbed his chin and sat back. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;Yes. that would fit. You say your mind is broken? This too is a common practice. Enchanters wipe someones mind so as to turn them into an obidient servant, as part of training them to be good slaves... Vivinne often did it. Beyond that, I cannot say.&quot;<br>
<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> That was that. Thenic had a new path to follow. He would confront these Sisters and find out what he could. And if that didn't work, he would search Qeynos and Freeport for the slavers. And if they didn't know anything, maybe an enchanter could undo what an enchanter had done.<br>
<br>
But the doubt was there. An evil idea, a horrible thought that gnawed at his soul. A what if of terrible proportions... It was brought by the reactions of those who knew him before he could remember. Their absolute hate and revultion at him. Even in pity they could barely tolerate his presense. What if he hadn't been a slave. What if this Sindeen or Sindeel was a dead end? What if the Sisters knew nothing of him, and had done nothing?<br>
<br>
<br>
What if... what if he had lost his memory on purpose to forget something. To forget the hate, the fear. <br>
<br>
<br>
He pushed this from his mind, and pushed on. He would find the one who tried to enslave him, who had cast the mind-charm that had robbed him of his life </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:yellow;font-family:verdana;font-size:small;">Thenic N'Ryt</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
